            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1465723424,
            "creation_date": 1465723330,
            "body": "<p>This here: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> if (!args.equals(null)){\n            String gen = generatePassword(args[1]);\n            return gen;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>just because args is not null, does this mean it has 2 elements?<\/p>\n\n<p>this here is not so a good idea:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String main(String[] args)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>because java has a method that looks like that\nso that coincidence is not allowing you to compile <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 37772632,
            "question_id": 37772557,
            "last_edit_date": 1465723424
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-polX-xM00NU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAADk/2ts3bPC4SQA/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 6012103,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4722232,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4722232/filom%c3%a9na-petr%c5%bel%c3%a9nov%c3%a1",
                "reputation": 313,
                "display_name": "Filom&#233;na Petržl&#233;nov&#225;",
                "accept_rate": 60
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1465723616,
            "creation_date": 1465723616,
            "body": "<p>Instead of checking <code>if (!args.equals(null))<\/code> do it like this <code>if (args != null)<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Then you should check if you have correct number of arguments, if you want to access <code>args[1]<\/code><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if(args.length == 2)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 37772671,
            "question_id": 37772557
        }
